  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>These will be short notes on the <fr:link href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NJ72iEPRXFk" type="external">video tutorial</fr:link> by <fr:link href="/sanjayshakkottai/" title="Sanjay Shakkottai" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/sanjayshakkottai/" display-uri="sanjayshakkottai" type="local">Sanjay Shakkottai</fr:link>. </html:p>
  
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/kellenkanarios/" title="Kellen Kanarios" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/kellenkanarios/" display-uri="kellenkanarios" type="local">Kellen Kanarios</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:title text="What is an SDE?">What is an SDE?</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
  First we have to discuss ODEs. For the ODE,
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[dx_t = \underbrace {\mu (x_t, t)}_{\text {``drift term''}} \mathrm {d}t]]></fr:tex>
  We have the following possible vector representation
  </html:p>

  <fr:resource hash="42c27a878fe3434c510289ff4214a269"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/42c27a878fe3434c510289ff4214a269.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[
  \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb, amsmath, stmaryrd}
 \ExplSyntaxOff
]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
  \begin {tikzpicture}
  \draw[->] (-1,0) -- (3,0) node[right] {$x$};
  \draw[->] (0,-1) -- (0,3) node[above] {$y$};
  \node[circle, orange, fill, inner sep=1pt] at (2,2) {} ;
  \node[orange] at (2.2,2.2) {$\boldsymbol {x_t}$};
  \draw[orange, ->, thick] (2, 2) -- (1.5,1.5) node[midway, below] {};
  \node[orange] at (2.2, 1.5)  {\footnotesize $\boldsymbol {\mu (x, t)}$};
  \end {tikzpicture}
]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource>

<html:p>This can be thought of as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_{t + h} - x_t \approx  \mu (x_t, t) \cdot  h + o(h)]]></fr:tex></html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  

  
